translations: n.（Killick）人名；（英）基利克；（瑞典）希利克

phrs.translation: 小锚, 石锚, 代用锚, 小艇锚

sentences.sentence: "Well, damn me if there are not a thousand places in the Thames more hazardous than this," Killick snorted.
sentences.translation: 基利克说：“哼，泰晤士河有一千处比这段河道还要危险。”

sentences.sentence: Captain Killick aboard the leading transport Goodwill angrily pushed the pilot aside and went forward to the forecastle to guide the ship through himself.
sentences.translation: 领队运输舰古德·威尔号船长基利克愤然把导航员推开，走到船楼上，亲自导航。
